column72: feedback. Here, you can give open feedback regarding concerns, improvement proposals and other thoughts.
I did get a little nervous when some pedestrians were crossing because the car was still going fast and if that pedestrian changed their course, might have gotten hit

There were times that I felt the car did not stop soon enough when it came across pedestrians jaywalking or a car parallel parking. The car slowed, but to my mind it slowed down too late. It should have slowed down earlier and come to a complete stop until the pedestrians competed crossing the street and the car completed parking.
Sometimes I felt like the automated vehicle got to close to other vehicles that were in front of it.

the vehicle came very close to a man crossing the street and didn`t seem to slow down. i would like to see speed, turn signals, and braking indicators to make better judgement calls in the videos. the vehicle comes very close to other vehicles and the crosswalks.
If felt as if the automated vehicle was speeding at times or the video had choppy moments. Also, there were a few times where pedestrians in the road color did not turn dark blue.
In this simulation all other vehicles were moving at a normal speed with no lag but the automated vehicle was kind of stuttering or lagging when moving.

Nothing comes to mind, the vehicle drove very well and was picking up everything extremely well. Even at times when vehicles were doing things unpredictable the automated driving seemed to recognize it.
N/A, Sorry I didn't read the N/A on previous times, but empty space meant N/A for me!
Enjoyable video, Its so different seeing the road threw an automated driving vehicle. Its interesting to say the least!
The eye tracker appeared to work well enough during calibration, but struggled during the 10 second test.
If another car were to stop at the front of the road, what would the automated vehicle do? Would it go around it or wait patiently until the other car at the front starts moving?
At the cinema the tram was not recognized.
Seemed to speed up when there were more pedestrians
I still think the lights above the pedestrians head is confusing and distracting.

I found the intensity of the colors far less distracting this time. I feel like they were more transparent or just less intense and that eased some of my nerves regarding not being able to clearly identify the colors of signs and lights. Overall it felt like a much smoother ride and I am feeling safer as I gain trust in the vehicle's ability.

Yesterdays videos seemed to have perfect timing, i guess you would call it.  But today the vehicle drove in the bicycle lane, too close to pedestrians at times and one time came too close for my liking to a car that was backing up
the vehicle needs to stop quicker and further back when people are crossing
